.TH "safe_hardlink_source" 9 "safe_hardlink_source" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
safe_hardlink_source \- Check for safe hardlink conditions
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" safe_hardlink_source
.BI "(struct user_namespace *mnt_userns "  ","
.BI "struct inode *inode "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mnt_userns" 12
user namespace of the mount the inode was found from
.IP "inode" 12
the source inode to hardlink from
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Return false if at least one of the following conditions:
- inode is not a regular file
- inode is setuid
- inode is setgid and group-exec
- access failure for read and write

Otherwise returns true.
